description_of_post: !!! This fundraising campaign by   is raising money for planes to head to Kabul and save as many people as possible. Their aim was half a million, now it‘s almost 4Mill and they are raising more money to allow planes to keep doing more turns.  Pls donate whatever u can and share this campaign wide and far!  I know ppl, who are ashamed of donating 5€, but please this helps. Every penny helps. U can donate anonymously. But give whatever you can give. Thank you Rob   🙏🏼 **** The individuals in question are high-value targets - Afghan men and women who have worked as human rights lawyers, champions of Women’s and LGBTQ rights, journalists, government liaisons, artists, and interpreters - all of whom are at imminent risk of being executed by the Taliban, along with their families. We will be taking full family units. If these people do not get rescued as soon as possible, neither they nor their family will make it through the month. The Taliban have a KILL LIST and are going door to door, searching for these people and reportedly killing them on sight if found.  THE MONEY: What happens to the money I donate? We want to be clear: EVERY SINGLE NICKEL of everything raised will go to either pay for flights, or support these humans through various non-profits - such as The International Women’s Media Organization (IWMF). Important note: EVERYONE VOLUNTEERING ON THIS PROJECT IS DOING SO FOR FREE. EVERY DOLLAR GOES BACK TO THESE AFGHAN REFUGEES. WE ARE NOT TAKING A PENNY. I think this is important to emphasize as we sadly live in a world where we have to worry about these things.                           ❤️❤️❤️

Liebe alle! Es passiert zur Zeit so viel in der Gesellschaft, dass es fast unmöglich ist, NICHT aktiv mitmischen zu wollen. Ich bin total leidenschaftlich, wenn es darum geht, für Gerechtigkeit und Gleichbehandlung aller Menschen einzutreten und ich hoffe ich bin nicht naiv, wenn ich denke, wirklich etwas bewirken zu können ... ein bisschen Zeit habe ich ja noch😁💪🏼💪🏼 ABER eigentlich melde ich mich, weil ich sagen wollte, dass es auch musikalisch gut läuft. Ich weiß, dass es von außen manchmal so aussieht, als würde sich gar nichts tun, aber das Gegenteil ist der Fall. So ein Karriereaufbau ist Knochenarbeit und glaubt mir: ihr wollt nicht alles wissen. Vor allem nicht, was alles schief laufen kann ;)  Am Ende des Tages bin ich einfach schon glücklich, DASS ES GUT LÄUFT und ich freu mich mega drauf, die Resultate mit euch zu teilen. …on Taliban Death List I watched a documentary about women, who are on death list of the Taliban those days.  The documentary also shows a school that the Taliban attacked and where 80 girls were killed.  While the brutal takeover of the Taliban affects ALL Afghan people it is again women and young girls, who are being targeted primarily and brutally tortured. They are being burned, hit, their skin is being peeled off alive, raped (as kids!) etc.  The link you find in my bio will organise rescue flights for as many Afghan men and women as possible (and their families), who are at imminent risk of being executed by the Taliban. Among them are people, who worked for the US as translators, intellectuals, artists, journalists, LGBTIQ+, human right lawyers, activists (like   and   ), etc.  What saddens me most is that while Afghanistan was completely f**** by the ‚West‘ the worst thing is that Afghan people feel like HOPE is gone. And imagine, hope is the very last thing that you cling on when there is nothing else left. This is cruel. And while politicians are busy checking their interests it is again on us to act as humans, show solidarity and push this matter - as we did with George Floyd, rip. As long as we care, people will have hope.  Pls share and donate - link in bio.                        🙌 Just sharing the concern each is then free to do what they want obviously...but i thought your followers may be interested to know that there are concerns Are the shown women safe? Please be careful with these private fundraisers as there is no indication that they will be able to in fact fly to and from Afghanistan. After 31 august there is no clarity on what will happen at the kabul airport (not that it's great now). Also GoFundMe is currently not releasing funds for Afghanistan projects

It’s HERSTORY and its EVERYBODY’S story! I believe in equality of EVERYBODY and I think that every single person has the right to live life as best as he/she/x can.  Life to me is about developing yourself and living your full potential. All this has nothing to do with gender. Yes, I do especially support young women and girls because I know that it is the group that is still not treated equally - and I will always support them.  BUT since I personally have long time ago stepped out of this thinking of gender roles etc. I want you to know that I always include everybody in my world, anytime - may it be female / male /  gender divers.  But politically I call myself a feminist and we do need equal rights for everybody. Therefore I go with one brilliant Austrian politician, Johanna Dohnal, who says that the vision of feminism is not about a female future. It is about a human future.  THERE YOU GO. BE HUMAN. BE FEMINISTS.                      Definitely Guuuuuuurl 🔥🔥🔥 👏👏👏

The situation in Afghanistan is dramatic, heartbraking and it is only getting worse. The Austrian Government is not only massively inhuman but delusional about their deportations. I can‘t imagine in what world they are living in. Shame on you.   found the right words and suggested that the Austrian Government should fly to Afghanistan to make a ‘reality check’.  Also Afghan women, children, journalists, artists, minorities and just everybody, who was and is fighting for the freedom of all people, has to be saved. Those people are the ones, who can actually change something in the future.  *      There is no path to peace without women. Have a look at the long, long history of women.  As an example: Aside from being hidden in their burqas, women’s names are not mentioned on official documents, invitation cards, … -  not even on their own grave(!).  Only in 2020 (!!!) women achieved to have their names printed alongside their fathers names in their childrens’ birth certificate / ID. This is just an example - and if you want to raise awareness use the hashtag   founded by Laleh Osmany   ❤️  says that women will go back to being objects.  The most cruel thing about the whole situation is that right now people do not even have hope. Therefore show solidarity.  And: get informed and educate. Because education is the most powerful weapon to change the situation.  Sources:                                             💯💯💯💯 Es ist herzzerreißend, zum Schreien, zum Verzweifeln was da gerade abgeht. Luftbrücken, Aufnahme von Flüchtlingen, Solidarität und schnelle Hilfe Unglaublich frustrierend und erschreckend was passiert, die Bilder sind furchtbar. Danke, dass du dir die Zeit für diesen Beitrag genommen hast.. Es ist nur schlimm was in Afghanistan durch die Machtübernahme der Taliban passiert. Obwohl man derzeit noch beteuert Frauenrechte, wie den Zugang zur Bildung zu respektieren, ist davon leider nicht auszugehen. Bitte nicht die gesamte Bundesregierung als inhuman zu bezeichnen, sondern vor allem den Innenminister Nehammer, welcher noch am Sonntag an den Abschiebungen nach Kabul festhalten wollte und nun Abschiebezentren in den Nachbarstaaten errichten möchte. Es ist die humane Pflicht Österreich Flüchtlingen einen sicheren Hafen hierzulande zu schaffen und für eine gerechte Verteilung von Flüchtlingen in Europa zu wirken. Und Nehammer bleibt herzlos..
